			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2012</a> paper:</span><br><i>Temporal Constraint Support for OCL</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/BilalKanso.html">Bilal Kanso</a>, <a href="../profile/SafouanTaha.html">Safouan Taha</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_6">10.1007/978-3-642-36089-3_6</a></li>
<li>Original shorter version of <a href="../sle2012s/paper07.html"><em>Specification of temporal properties with OCL</em></a> (SLE 2012 SI)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagM">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It provides a formal, scenario-based semantics for temporal constraints on OCL and links this to formal-methods practice.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5c.html"><span class="tagL">T5C: Testing</span></a><ul><li> Temporal constraints are explicitly connected to automatic test generation via test purposes derived from the constraints.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> A key practical contribution is an implementation integrated into the Eclipse/MDT OCL tooling.
</li></ul></li></ul>
